    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think we should be able to do this, but it can be difficult to distinguish between class methods and unbound methods on compiled types, and we want to be sure that for compiled objects we don't misinterpret the presence of `_ipython_display_` as being defined for the class instead of instances. If we restrict it to Python classes, it should be possible.\n"
